						               													<description>Replay your favorite team's entire 2020 schedule in about an hour!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A simulation of the pro game, D20 Football reduces the NFL to its most basic level. Each team is rated for offense and defense based on points scored and yielded &amp;ndash; including all defensive and special team scoring. Ultimately, the only statistic that matters is point differential &amp;ndash; and that's what counts in D20 Football.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game play is simple: for each quarter, the players use a virtual 20-sided die chit-pull system and consult the results chart. If no overtime, that's just four &amp;quot;die rolls&amp;quot; per scheduled game per player. Luck isn't everything, though. Players choose an offensive and defensive focus for each quarter. The player who does the better job of outwitting his opponent can affect the results in his favor to a considerable degree.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;So, can 2020&amp;rsquo;s Tampa Bay Bucs go all the way in your replay? Maybe not &amp;ndash; there are four slightly better teams in their way.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every 2020 NFL team is rated, and a specially designed scoresheet makes the game flow smoothly. The game can be played solo or two-player. It&amp;rsquo;s highly portable, easy to play, and is sure to &amp;ldquo;fire up&amp;rdquo; football fans of all ages.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
